Description: I am thinning out my very large collection of stringed instruments (numbering nearly 200), which I began in the 1970's. This is a beautiful TCM Empress solidbody guitar from 2001. The condition is near mint--only a few small scratches on the back & very minor finish checking on the top. Beautiful sunburst color. AAAA flame maple top. Pickup configuration is SSH. The following is from the TCM website: The Empress is essentially a hybrid of the two most popular electric guitars in the world…with a host of unique features. While it’s true that this guitar can produce many of our favorite vintage tones of the past, what is really interesting are the new sounds you’ll be inventing on your Empress.This is a very snappy, articulate instrument that responds quickly to picking and fretting nuances at all volume levels.The Empress features a AAAA figured maple carved top and chambered mahogany back with reinforced mahogany neck, TCM Vibe and Sperzel keys.Beautiful paua shell “rope” inlays on a select Indian rosewood fretboard are standard.Features new noiseless “single coils”and our TCM Zodiac humbucker in the bridge.1 TCM Single coil neck, 1 TCM Single coil middle and TCM Zodiac bridge humbucker, uncovered.1 volume control.1 tone control.Volume controls have high pass clarity circuit which preserves tone at lower volume levels.5 way switch yields the following tones:Position 1 Neck single coil:Wirey, liquid-like tones...perfect for "Texas Blues" or soaring, Hendrix-like styles.Position 2 Neck and middle single coils:Hum-canceling. Enough "quack" when driven, yet almost acoustic like when clean.Position 3 Middle single coil:Finally, a middle position single coil that sounds great on its own. A remarkably full rangetone.Position 4 Middle single coil and bridge humbucker:Hum-canceling. Lots of "quack". Sounds great at any volume or gain setting.Position 5 Bridge humbucker in series:Full bore snarling TCM Zodiac humbucker drive and sustain. This guitar has several upgrades, including gold hardware and matching maple figured headstock. Original iconic TCM green hardshell case. Free shipping to CONUS addresses.
